mixin section-process
  section.section&attributes(attributes)
    .container-fluid
      .container.container--gradient
        +bullet(4, 'process').js-item-animation

        h2.title.js-item-animation This is how the technology works in a nutshell
        .item.js-item-animation
          .item__cell
            p.item__id 01
          .item__cell
            .item__picture
              +picture('synthetics/work-1', 'Work 1')
          .item__cell
            .item__icon
              svg(width='25' height='23' viewBox='0 0 25 23' fill='none' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg')
                path(d='M0 11.8946L22.8816 11.8946' stroke='#282828' stroke-width='3')
                path(d='M12.9843 21.7891L22.8789 11.8946L12.9843 2' stroke='#282828' stroke-width='3')
          .item__cell
            p.item__text First, you need to have a photo taken (source photo) on a real human model or mannequin.

        .item.js-item-animation
          .item__cell
            p.item__id 02
          .item__cell
            .item__picture
              +picture('synthetics/work-2', 'Work 2')
          .item__cell
            .item__icon
              svg(width='25' height='23' viewBox='0 0 25 23' fill='none' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg')
                path(d='M0 11.8946L22.8816 11.8946' stroke='#282828' stroke-width='3')
                path(d='M12.9843 21.7891L22.8789 11.8946L12.9843 2' stroke='#282828' stroke-width='3')
          .item__cell
            p.item__text Second, Mannequin Synthetics identifies the apparel and the human in the photo.

        .item.js-item-animation
          .item__cell
            p.item__id 03
          .item__cell
            .item__picture
              +picture('synthetics/work-3', 'Work 3')
          .item__cell
            .item__icon
              svg(width='25' height='23' viewBox='0 0 25 23' fill='none' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg')
                path(d='M0 11.8946L22.8816 11.8946' stroke='#282828' stroke-width='3')
                path(d='M12.9843 21.7891L22.8789 11.8946L12.9843 2' stroke='#282828' stroke-width='3')
          .item__cell
            p.item__text Third, Mannequin Synthetics creates a digital model and blends it nicely with the apparel in the photo.

        .block.js-item-animation
          h4 That’s not all. What if you didn’t need any staff whatsoever? What if your photoshooting process could be fully automatic, or fully remote? Imagine never having to talk to a union rep again.
